{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\nToday a plan-review criterion is inert unless it is in the hardcoded `CANONICAL_LLM` frozenset\n(`plan_review/registry.py:70`) AND the packaged `criteria_routing.json`; `_routing_index()` /\n`load_criteria()` are `@lru_cache`d with no `repo_root` key. So a project cannot add a criterion at\nall. This story opens the vocabulary and adds the project overlay — the **dependency root + MVP\nslice** for the whole epic (`3156`). It is NOT blocked on `b744` (extends plan-review directly).\n\n## What\n\n- `effective_criteria(repo_root)` = `CANONICAL_LLM` ∪ activated project ids; route it through\n  **every** plan-review vocabulary site: `load_criteria`, `check_registry_coverage`, and the\n  workflow Pass-1 batch vocab in `workflow_ops` (`plan_review_assemble_criteria`). The\n  `include_<id>` output key must sanitize the `project.<name>` id (`.`→`_`) at BOTH the assemble\n  and consume sites (keep the rule co-located).\n- `.rebar/criteria_routing.json` overlay: gate-keyed (`{plan_review: {...}, activate: [...]}`),\n  reusing the packaged routing schema; `project.<name>` namespace; an un-prefixed built-in id =\n  re-tune/disable; a `project.`-id colliding with a built-in, or a duplicate, is **rejected at\n  load** (located error). A criterion runs only if in `activate`.\n- Cache isolation: keep `_routing_index()` cached for the packaged index; add\n  `effective_routing(repo_root)` (uncached, or keyed by `(repo_root, overlay mtime)` — note mtime\n  granularity, prefer content hash if flaky); extend `prompt_library._invalidate_caches()`.\n- Routing validation: load-time (invalid routing = located error, not silent skip) + a CI\n  drift/parity gate mirroring `reviewers/index.json`.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Files: `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/registry.py`, `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/workflow_ops.py`,\n  `src/rebar/llm/prompt_library.py`, `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/criteria_routing.json` (schema doc).\n- MVP end-to-end: activate ONE project LLM criterion from the overlay → it runs in plan-review\n  Pass-1 → surfaces a finding. (Attestation invalidation is story `#4`; unify is story `#6`.)\n- Out: code-review side (story `#6`, b744-blocked); DET consumer (story `#2`).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `effective_criteria(repo_root)` loads activated project criteria and is routed through\n      `load_criteria`, `check_registry_coverage`, and the workflow Pass-1 batch vocab; an activated\n      project LLM criterion fans out and runs in plan-review Pass-1.\n- [ ] `.rebar/criteria_routing.json` overlay per schema: gate-keyed, `project.<name>` namespace,\n      explicit `activate` list, load-time collision/rebind rejection (located error).\n- [ ] `include_<id>` key sanitization (`.`→`_`) applied at both assemble + consume sites.\n- [ ] Overlay merge is cache-isolated per repo (packaged index stays cached; overlay is not);\n      a RED test proves no cross-repo routing leakage in the long-lived MCP server.\n- [ ] Routing validation: invalid overlay routing is a located error + a CI drift/parity gate.\n- [ ] An ADR documents the unified-registry + overlay merge/activation contract.\n- [ ] MVP slice demonstrated end-to-end (activate one criterion → runs → surfaces a finding).\n\n## Backward-compatibility, fan-out mechanism & cache strategy (remediation, run 1)\n\n### Expand-contract / backward-compatibility (clears T4)\nEvery signature change is **additive** with a `repo_root=None` default that preserves\ntoday's behaviour, so no existing caller breaks:\n- `registry.load_criteria(repo_root=None)`, `registry.by_id(repo_root=None)`,\n  `registry.check_registry_coverage(repo_root=None)`, `registry._descriptor_from_prompt(cid,\n  *, repo_root=None, routing_index=None)`, and the NEW `effective_criteria(repo_root=None)` /\n  `effective_routing(repo_root=None)` all default `repo_root=None`.\n- `repo_root=None` resolves to `config.repo_root()` (the same root `get_prompt` already\n  resolves `.rebar/prompts/` overrides against) — so an **overlay-absent** repo yields\n  **exactly** today's packaged-only vocabulary/routing (no behaviour change, no churn).\n- **Call sites updated** (enumerated): `orchestrator.route_criteria` (passes the ctx\n  repo_root), `workflow_ops.plan_review_assemble_criteria` (uses `ctx.repo_root`),\n  `attest.registry_version`/`plan_review.__init__` coverage (story #4 threads repo_root;\n  this story keeps the no-arg default working), and the tests. Bare `load_criteria()` /\n  `check_registry_coverage()` keep working unchanged.\n- **Rollback:** delete `.rebar/criteria_routing.json` (overlay-absent ⇒ packaged behaviour),\n  or revert the additive params (all default `None`).\n\n### Dynamic Pass-1 fan-out mechanism (clears G6/T1/T3 — schema-safe, NO v3 change)\nThe v3 `batch` step schema (`workflow.v3.schema.json`) is IMMUTABLE + version-pinned with\n`additionalProperties:false` on `$defs/batch`, and the gate validates its OWN document at run\ntime — so a new `batch` field (e.g. `extra_criteria`) is impossible without a v4 schema+shim\n(out of MVP scope). Instead, project criteria fan out through the **rebar-specific\n`ProductionBatchRunner`** (`production_batch_runner.py`), NOT a new doc field:\n- built-in criteria keep fanning out via the STATIC `criteria:` list in `gates/plan-review.yaml`\n  (each gated by its `include_<ID>` key — byte-identical to today);\n- the runner, after `assemble_context`, calls `route_criteria(ctx)` (which now returns the FULL\n  effective set) and appends ONLY the `project.<name>`-prefixed descriptors — already past the\n  SAME `applies()`/overlay filter the built-ins use — to the finder's tier-split set, deduped\n  against the built-ins. `assemble` still emits sanitized `include_project_<name>` booleans\n  (`.`→`_`) as the coverage/routing record. `gates/plan-review.yaml` and the immutable schema\n  are UNTOUCHED. (Probe-mode caveat: route_criteria has no probe notion, so a project criterion\n  is also evaluated during a drift probe — harmless, documented follow-up.)\n\n### Cache strategy — content-hash, not mtime (clears E2/G6/T8/T9)\n`effective_routing`/`load_criteria` are memoized in repo-keyed module dicts keyed by\n`(repo_root, sha256(overlay-bytes))` — a **content signature**, NOT mtime (mtime\ngranularity is coarse/flaky), so editing the overlay auto-invalidates the memo. The\npackaged `_routing_index()` stays `@lru_cache`d (immutable per binary). Stale-entry\ngrowth is bounded: `prompt_library._invalidate_caches()` clears both memos + the lru_caches\n(the RED cross-repo-leak test proves repo A's routing never serves repo B).\n\n### Sanitization inverse & missing-prompt fallback (clears T8)\nThe `.`→`_` map is one-directional at the workflow-key layer only; the criterion id and\nprompt id retain the dotted form, so no inverse un-sanitization is needed (the\n`project_criteria` entry carries the real dotted `prompt` id directly). An activated\nproject id whose prompt file is absent/malformed surfaces as a **located `RegistryError`**\nfrom `load_criteria` (same as a missing built-in prompt) — fail-loud at load, never a\nsilent skip.\n\n### ADR contents (clears E1/AC6)\n`docs/adr/0015-project-supplied-criteria.md` documents: the `.rebar/criteria_routing.json`\noverlay schema (gate-keyed, `project.<name>` namespace, `activate` list); the merge +\ncollision/rebind rules; `effective_criteria`/`effective_routing` as the vocabulary seam;\nthe content-hash cache-isolation contract; and the runner-side (schema-free) project fan-out.\n\n### Scope clarification (clears E5/T8/G5)\nFiles also touched: `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/production_batch_runner.py` (project fan-in) and `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/orchestrator.py` (`route_criteria` threads repo_root). MVP end-to-end exercises ONE activated project **LLM** criterion (`exec: 1-TURN`). Project\n`exec: DET` criteria (the prompt-less descriptor branch) are story #2; the shared\n`rebar.llm.criteria` unification is story #6. The CI drift/parity gate here is a\n**validation** gate (the packaged `criteria_routing.json` stays schema-valid and in parity\nwith `CANONICAL_LLM` + the prompt files), not a generator, since the routing is\nhand-authored judgement (thresholds/applies_at) with no derivation source.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria (remediation additions)\n\n- [ ] All new/changed registry signatures are additive with a `repo_root=None` default that\n      preserves packaged-only behaviour (overlay-absent repo == today); rollback = delete the\n      overlay.\n- [ ] The dynamic Pass-1 fan-out for a project criterion is runner-side (`ProductionBatchRunner`\n      appends the `project.` subset of `route_criteria`), leaving the immutable v3 `batch` schema\n      and `gates/plan-review.yaml` UNCHANGED.\n\n- [ ] An activated project criterion with a missing/malformed prompt file raises a LOCATED\n      `RegistryError` from `load_criteria` (fail-loud, no silent skip); a test asserts it.\n- [ ] Overlay mis-authoring is covered by named tests: collision/rebind rejection, un-namespaced\n      net-new id, activated-without-routing, invalid routing schema, malformed JSON — each a\n      located `RegistryError`.\n- [ ] `prompt_library._invalidate_caches()` clears the new overlay-merged caches (proven: an\n      overlay edit is picked up for the same repo_root without a process restart).\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782876959678400001,"uuid":"1ffd3c55-d50d-49c8-8f8f-09aaa93b3e58"}